Title: Object: Repose in Egypt
Description: The Holy Family resting on the way to Egypt, sitting with bushes behind to right, pyramids in the distance to left, St Joseph reading, the Virgin holding the sleeping infant Jesus on her lap, resting her chin on His head; state before conversion to an etching, and 'A.M. Sct.' crossed out. c. 1776, this state c. 1790 Etching and aquatint with roulette, printed in brown ink
Bibliographic references: Pressly / The Life and Art of James Barry (4.I)
Acquisition name: Purchased from: A E Evans & Sons
